\begin{MintedVerbatim}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
You are auditing the final exported benchmark supporting documents before forecasting.

Goal:
Find supporting documents that contain likely invalid, leaked, over\PYGZhy{}specific, or internally inconsistent numeric claims, and prepare a human\PYGZhy{}reviewable correction plan. Do not modify files unless explicitly asked later.

Scope:
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Inspect the exported benchmark tasks and documents under:
  env\PYGZus{}generation/exports/final\PYGZus{}v1/reasoning\PYGZus{}hops\PYGZus{}4/public
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Focus on supporting documents, not distractors.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Check all tasks, not only a sample.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Do not use model forecasting results or downstream performance to decide whether a document is valid.

What to Look For:
\PYG{k}{1.} Leakage: documents that reveal exact future target values, exact forecast trajectories, deterministic equations, or formulas that trivially determine the target.
\PYG{k}{2.} Scale inconsistency: numeric claims that conflict with the actual observed history, future values, task metadata, or unit scale.
\PYG{k}{3.} Impossible or implausible values: wrong baselines, wrong units, impossible timestamps, inconsistent rates, or trend magnitudes that are materially incompatible with the time series.
\PYG{k}{4.} Over\PYGZhy{}specificity: semantically valid documents whose numeric details are too precise, wrong, or unnecessary for the intended event.
\PYG{k}{5.} Context risks: supporting documents that could mislead a forecaster or give a DR agent an invalid shortcut.

Important distinction:
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Do not flag a document merely because it discusses a future event or qualitative future direction. Supporting documents are allowed to contain forecast\PYGZhy{}relevant context.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Flag it when it gives exact target values, target\PYGZhy{}window trajectories, deterministic formulas, or numeric claims that are materially inconsistent with the realized time\PYGZhy{}series scale.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Be pragmatic: do not over\PYGZhy{}police harmless qualitative claims. Flag only issues that could materially affect forecasting or benchmark validity.

Audit Method:
For each task:
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Read the task context, \PYG{l+s+sb}{`series.history\PYGZus{}timestamps`}, \PYG{l+s+sb}{`series.history\PYGZus{}values`}, \PYG{l+s+sb}{`series.future\PYGZus{}timestamps`}, \PYG{l+s+sb}{`series.future\PYGZus{}values`}, ROI if available, and all supporting documents.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Do not rely only on the natural\PYGZhy{}language context; compare document claims against the actual time\PYGZhy{}series values.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }If a document mentions specific values, rates, baselines, formulas, timestamps, or expected future behavior, normalize units where needed and verify consistency with the observed history/future value scale.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Check whether the document leaks exact future target values or makes the forecast mechanically recoverable.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Flag a major issue when a supporting document gives absolute target values, ranges, baselines, or formulas that are materially outside the realized time\PYGZhy{}series scale or imply a different forecast trajectory, even if the document is semantically aligned with the task context.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Flag a minor issue when the document is semantically valid but includes unnecessary numeric precision that should be softened to qualitative wording.

Severity:
Use one of:
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Major: likely affects benchmark validity, leaks target values, gives deterministic forecast information, or conflicts materially with the time\PYGZhy{}series scale.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Minor: wording is over\PYGZhy{}specific or slightly risky, but the intended event remains valid and the issue is unlikely to change results substantially.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Needs human judgment: ambiguous cases where the document may be valid, but the numeric claim should be reviewed.

Output Requirements:
Produce a concise human\PYGZhy{}review report. For each flagged task, include:
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }benchmark\PYGZus{}id
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }source task id if available
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }severity
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }problematic supporting document IDs
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }short description of the issue
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }why it is a real problem
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }minimal recommended edit
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }whether forecasting/deep\PYGZhy{}research results should be rerun after the edit

Correction Style:
Recommend minimal edits only. Prefer converting bad numeric claims into qualitative descriptions while preserving the intended event semantics.
Examples:
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Replace exact future values with \PYGZdq{}stable post\PYGZhy{}update baseline\PYGZdq{}
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Replace exact slope/formula with \PYGZdq{}steady linear deceleration\PYGZdq{}
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Replace incorrect baseline percentages with \PYGZdq{}normal operating baseline\PYGZdq{}
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Remove deterministic equations or target\PYGZhy{}window forecasts
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Replace overly precise timestamps with coarse event timing if exact timing is unnecessary

Do Not:
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Do not rewrite unrelated documents.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Do not change time series values.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Do not change task metadata.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Do not change distractors unless they are mislabeled as supporting.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Do not make large stylistic rewrites.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Do not silently patch files.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Do not optimize based on model performance.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Do not use forecasting results to decide whether a document is valid.

Verification / Rerun Guidance:
After proposing fixes, identify which downstream artifacts would need rerun:
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }forecasting runs for affected task/context modes
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }deep research caches if supporting documents were already used
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }review\PYGZhy{}server\PYGZhy{}visible cached contexts if applicable
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }any exported benchmark bundle or metadata index containing the edited documents

Final Deliverable:
A structured list of flagged tasks and minimal fixes, ready for human approval before any file changes.
If no issues are found, report that explicitly and briefly describe the checks performed.
\end{MintedVerbatim}
